    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers observations of a single dominant register: the direct, first-person founder voice, mostly Scarlet's, captured verbatim. The mainline is unhedged and declarative — corrections land flat ([restate-then-replace](narr:StyleObs_DirectCorrection)), policies use bare imperatives ([no-hedge rules](narr:StyleObs_DirectImperative)), and conviction shows as short present-tense assertions ([VC-plan declarative](narr:StyleObs_FirstPersonDeclarative), [B2C self-distillation](narr:StyleObs_ScarletDistillation)). Authenticity is signaled mechanically: Markdown blockquotes set founder speech apart from analytical prose ([dual-register memos](narr:StyleObs_DirectPersonalTone_DesignSession)), and prospect/founder quotes are treated as evidence, not anecdote ([show-don't-tell](narr:StyleObs_DirectQuoteEvidence)). Profanity recurs as a candor and decisiveness marker ([launch-date frustration](narr:StyleObs_ProfanityDecisiveness), [sqlite regret](narr:StyleObs_FrustratedVoiceQuote)). A parallel second-person mode keeps the prospect in frame ([you/your pitch](narr:StyleObs_SecondPerson), [confront-and-intimate](narr:StyleObs_DirectSecondPerson)). Em-dash pivots and staccato fragments recur as cadence ([assertion-then-reframe](narr:StyleObs_EmDashRhetoric)). Across the span: brand stylization, sales testimony, design-session diagnosis, and product-positioning corrections all sit under the same direct-personal banner.""" ;
